claim.claim-text:
An air purification system (100), comprising:
an airflow channel (104) including an inlet (126) and an outlet (128);
a support (130) disposed in the airflow channel (104);
a photocatalyst (132) on the support (130) disposed to contact airflow through the airflow channel (104) passing across or through the support (130);
an ultraviolet light emitting diode (136) disposed to emit ultraviolet light onto the photocatalyst (132);
a power source (114) selectively electrically connected to the ultraviolet light emitting diode (136) to provide current to the ultraviolet light emitting diode (136) at a duty cycle, the duty cycle in response to a duty cycle control signal; and
a controller (116) configured to generate the duty cycle control signal at least in part as a function of a desired minimum volatile organic compound conversion rate of air flowing through the airflow channel (104) and a desired maximum by-product concentration in air flowing through the outlet (128) of the airflow channel (104).

The air purification system (100) of claim 1,

further comprising a volatile organic compound concentration feedback device (118) configured to generate an air quality feedback signal indicative of a concentration of volatile organic compounds in air flowing into the inlet (126) of the airflow channel (104); the volatile organic compound feedback device (118) including at least one of;

a carbon dioxide sensor (142);

a volatile organic compound sensor (144); and

a user input device (146) for inputting the air quality feedback signal; and

wherein the controller (116) is configured to generate the duty cycle control signal at least in part as a function of the air quality feedback signal.

A method for purifying air, comprising:
directing air through an inlet (126) of an airflow channel (104);
determining a desired minimum volatile organic compound conversion rate of the air;
determining a desired maximum by-product concentration in the air when it flows through an outlet (128) of the airflow channel (104);
generating with a controller (116), a power control signal indicative of a desired power duty cycle of an ultraviolet light emitting diode (136), the desired duty cycle determined, at least in part, as a function of the desired minimum volatile organic compound conversion rate and the desired maximum by-product concentration;
powering the ultraviolet light emitting diode (136) at the desired duty cycle;
directing the air into contact with a photocatalyst (132), the photocatalyst (132) disposed in the airflow channel (104); and
irradiating the photocatalyst (132) with ultraviolet light from the ultraviolet light emitting diode (136).

The method of claim 6, further comprising;

determining a desired frequency of the duty cycle of the ultraviolet light emitting diode (136) at least in part as a function of the desired minimum volatile organic compound conversion rate and the desired maximum by-product concentration; and

irradiating the photocatalyst (132) with ultraviolet light from the ultraviolet light emitting diode (136) at the desired duty cycle at the desired frequency.

The method of any or more of claims 6-7, further comprising;

determining a desired current level to supply the ultraviolet light emitting diode (136) at least in part as a function of the desired minimum volatile organic compound conversion rate and the desired maximum by-product concentration; and

supplying the ultraviolet light emitting diode (136) with current at the desired current level.

An aircraft (102) air purification system (100), comprising:
an aircraft cabin (108),
an airflow channel (104) including an inlet (126) and an outlet (128), both the inlet (126) and the outlet (128) fluidly connected to the cabin (108);
a support (130) disposed in the airflow channel (104);
a photocatalyst (132) on the support (130) disposed to contact airflow through the airflow channel (104) passing across or through the support (130);
an ultraviolet light emitting diode (136) disposed to emit ultraviolet light onto the photocatalyst (132);
a power source (114) selectively electrically connected to the ultraviolet light emitting diode (136) to provide current to the ultraviolet light emitting diode (136) at a duty cycle, the duty cycle in response to a duty cycle control signal
